89/* A couple of flags that basic/legacy_setup can support. */
90#define TT_NEED_SOCKETPAIR TT_FIRST_USER_FLAG
91#define TT_NEED_BASE (TT_FIRST_USER_FLAG<<1)
92#define TT_NEED_DNS (TT_FIRST_USER_FLAG<<2)
93#define TT_LEGACY (TT_FIRST_USER_FLAG<<3)
94#define TT_NEED_THREADS (TT_FIRST_USER_FLAG<<4)
95#define TT_NO_LOGS (TT_FIRST_USER_FLAG<<5)
96#define TT_ENABLE_IOCP_FLAG (TT_FIRST_USER_FLAG<<6)
97#define TT_ENABLE_IOCP (TT_ENABLE_IOCP_FLAG|TT_NEED_THREADS)
98
99/* All the flags that a legacy test needs. */
100#define TT_ISOLATED TT_FORK|TT_NEED_SOCKETPAIR|TT_NEED_BASE
101
102
103#define BASIC(name,flags) \
104 { #name, test_## name, flags, &basic_setup, NULL }
105
106#define LEGACY(name,flags) \
107 { #name, run_legacy_test_fn, flags|TT_LEGACY, &legacy_setup, \
108 test_## name }

110struct evutil_addrinfo;
111struct evutil_addrinfo *ai_find_by_family(struct evutil_addrinfo *ai, int f);
112struct evutil_addrinfo *ai_find_by_protocol(struct evutil_addrinfo *ai, int p);
113int test_ai_eq_(const struct evutil_addrinfo *ai, const char *sockaddr_port,
114 int socktype, int protocol, int line);
115
116#define test_ai_eq(ai, str, s, p) do { \
117 if (test_ai_eq_((ai), (str), (s), (p), __LINE__)<0) \
118 goto end; \
119 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
120
121#define test_timeval_diff_leq(tv1, tv2, diff, tolerance) \
122 tt_int_op(labs(timeval_msec_diff((tv1), (tv2)) - diff), <=, tolerance)
123
124#define test_timeval_diff_eq(tv1, tv2, diff) \
125 test_timeval_diff_leq((tv1), (tv2), (diff), 50)
126
127long timeval_msec_diff(const struct timeval *start, const struct timeval *end);
